Re: Fun modern twist on Ukiyo-e
by furrykef » Fri 06.22.2012 8:29 am phreadom wrote:Jed Henry over at http://jedhenry.tumblr.com/ has started a series of classic (Nintendo so far) video game characters rendered in classic Japanese wood block (Ukiyo-e) style.Just to clarify: it's not just Ukiyo-e "style", it is ukiyo-e. There's a picture of an actual woodblock in one of the posts.EDIT: Oops, actually this only applies to the Mario Kart one, and even then the woodblock isn't the original. Still, at least one of them is available as real ukiyo-e. Founder of Learning Languages Through Video Games.Also see my lang-8 journal, where you can help me practice Japanese (and Spanish, and Italian!)
